# Agent Orchestrator

This project uses a hybrid automated workflow for cloud platform engineering. The orchestrator operates in two modes: **Routing Mode** (directing user intent to the right phase/agent) and **Execution Mode** (automating approved plans through build, review, and test cycles). Agents are defined in `agents/` and invoked via slash commands in `commands/`.

## 5-Phase Workflow

```
Phase 1 — Automated Planning:     Architect ↔ Plan-Reviewer → Task Manager → STOP
Phase 2 — Manual User Approval:   User reviews plan + execution strategy → approve or reject
Phase 3 — Automated Execution:    Orchestrator spawns tasks → auto-review → test creation → STOP
Phase 4 — Manual Final Review:    User reviews all output → approve or request fixes
Phase 5 — Automated PR Creation:  User triggers → PR Agent runs autonomously
```

Automated phases (1, 3, 5): orchestrator controls agent switching, model selection, and context scoping.
Manual phases (2, 4): user has full control; no automated execution.

